Perform portfolio analysis to identify potential credit risks and provide professional advice on risk mitigation. Gather and analyse market information, monitor the performance of credit facilities utilization to identify early signs of credit deterioration. Perform impairment assessment, conduct procedural reviews and relevant MIS reports. Make recommendations and review on credit risk management strategies to comply with relevant regulatory requirements.

Requirements:

Degree holder in Risk Management, Finance, Economics, Accounting, Information System or related disciplines;
At least 3 years experience in credit risk management and monitoring;
Sound knowledge in legal and regulatory requirements, Basel III and banking practices on credit risk management;
Hands-on experience of MS Excel, PowerPoint (Knowledge in database management and statistical computer applications is an advantage);
Analytical, independent with good communication skills;
Proficient in both spoken and written English and Chinese.

(Candidate with less experience will be considered as Assistant Credit Monitoring Manager.)

If you are flexible enough and zeal for a harmonious and supportive working environment where enables you to grow and succeed professionally, please send a full resume indicating your public examination results (HKCEE and HKALE / HKDSE), your present and expected salary and quoting reference number attention to Talent Acquisition Division, Nanyang Commercial Bank, 151 Des Voeux Road Central, Hong Kong or apply through email. For details, please visit https://www.ncb.com.hk/ and select the page Recruit.

We are an Equal Opportunities Employer. Data collected would be used for recruitment purposes only. Applicants who do not hear from us within 8 weeks may consider their applications unsuccessful and their data will be destroyed within 12 months of receipt.

Job Responsibilities

Assist to prepare and review F&B items and store inventories;
Conduct inventory check on F&B and operating equipment items;
Prepare daily costing reports;
Participate in month-end closing;
Assist to income audit matters and daily accounting activities;
Prepare and perform control activities for operation;
Assist other ad hoc assignments as assigned.

Requirements

Degree / Diploma holder in Accounting, Hospitality or related discipline;
Minimum 3 years related experience;
Previous experience in Hospitality industry would be an advantageous;
Proficiency in MS Office applications;
Good command in both written and spoken English and Mandarin;
Knowledge of PMS system (Opera) and POS system would be advantageous;
Less experience will be considered as Senior Finance Clerk.

Why Spacebox?

Spacebox is the leading on-demand storage Company in Hong Kong. See how our service works HERE. We provide an outstanding service that helps Hong Kong people make the most of the space they have.

We have been successful because we are committed to our clients and to our team. This is a Company that offers a space to thrive and do your best work in a highly supportive environment.

Our mission is to transform the storage industry in Hong Kong and to be the industry leader. When we started there were exactly zero customer centric companies in this industry. We are proud to have changed this and we continue to push ourselves to set new standards every day.


What you’ll be doing?

Manage Account Receivable operations: payment methods, payment processors, billing system, dunning & collection process, bad debt and write off process;
Develop, document, and maintain Billing, AR & Collections policies;
Guide and supervise daily performance of billing and credit officers: distribute targets and assure performance, train and develop as required;
Ensure billing and client database accuracy and drive process improvement and automation efforts to streamline revenue reconciliation and accounting;
Monitor DSO and Average Collection Period to determine if adjustments to collection policies are necessary;
Work closely with management and all other departments to continuously improve company AR collection results;
Provide world-class customer service to external and internal customers (i.e., Sales, Customer Success, Operations, etc);
Collaborate with the IT team on automation and enhancement projects to continuously improve processes;
Manage month-end close tasks, including income recognition and P&L income side accuracy;
Support management on cash forecasting, provide management with regular AR performance metrics and other ad-hoc reports;
Support ad hoc projects and assignments as required.

Who we are looking for?

You have at least 6 years working experience in accounting, with 3 years in account receivable and at least 2 years in a supervisory function.
Experience in high volume AR environment, subscription billing experience preferred;
Comfortable with ambiguity and comfortable in a fast-paced, evolving environment;
Strong understanding of operational accounting procedures and month-end and quarter-end close processes;
Qualification of HKICPA, ACCA or equivalent will be an advantage, other recognised CPA qualification will be considered;
Proficient in advanced excel and accounting systems, at ease with adopting new IT platforms;
Strong interpersonal communication skills;
Fluent in English.

Key Roles and Responsibilities 

Responsible for Accounts duties, including handling daily transactions, data input and processing, compilation of report etc;
Coordinate with other departments in Accounts issues;
Assist in handling book-keeping and accounting tasks; &
Ad hoc tasks as assigned.

 Qualification and Experience

Form 5 or above, with LCCI 2nd Level or above;
At least 1-2 year's relevant working experience would be preferable;
Familiar with MS Office, especially in excel;
Experience of working with FLEX Accounting system is a definite advantage; &
Immediately available is highly preferable.

