Vickmans LaboratoriesLimited is an Equal Opportunities Employer. Personal data provided by job applicants will be used strictly in accordance with our personal data policy and for recruitment purposes only. We aim to respond to successful applicants within 8 weeks and related information will be kept in our file for up to 12 months for other suitable vacancies in our organization and thereafter destroyed

Responsibilities:

Assures consistent quality of service by developing and enforcing good Facilities Management (FM) and Customer Service (CS) operation manuals, procedures and guidelines (SOP).
Reviews, evaluates, and analyzes complex information for the purpose of ensuring the department meets established quality standards and remains compliant.
Strictly adhere to and comply with HKSTP Corporate policies, regulations and statutory requirements;
Verifies accuracy of documents submitted from service providers and CFM colleagues to determine eligibility, and accuracy of reporting according to the HKSTP Corporate Policy and Procedures.
Provides regular tracking of file submissions and effectively communicates outcomes and findings of case reviews with Internal Audits (IA) and ICAC.
Effectively manages all CFM caseload and meets established performance targets, while adhering to HKSAR regulatory and statutory requirements with timely follow-up.
Validate CFM processes and procedures through auditing and quality assurance reviews.
Facilitate problem-solving discussions with a focus on quality improvement.
Organizes data into a logical format for presentation and in written reports as requested by management.
Facilitate and participate in routine meetings with other staff members and management to discuss the accuracy of report submissions.
Provide and compile accurate data and information to management for internal use upon request.
Develop, track and submit KPI information in management reporting format.
Formulate strategic improvement plan for the betterment of service level improvements and operational effectiveness of CFM.
Acquires and maintains up to date trackers for all statutory required licenses and services.
Perform other duties as assigned by Senior Manager, Associate Director, Director of Corporate Facilities Management and Head of Operations and Leasing.

Requirements:

University degree and above in Building Studies, Property / Facilities Management, Finance, Cost Control or relevant field is preferred;
Minimum 5 years’ experience working in quality assurance and facilities management or related field;
Experience in Facilities Management Services operations, and expose to the latest CRM, technology of intelligent building and conversant with FM-Maintenance Management System and related systems and software is preferred;
Corporate membership of ISO Management System, HKIS, RICS or equivalent is an added advantage;
Proficiency in both written and spoken English and Chinese (including Putonghua);
Exceptionally well organized with an aptitude for data and possess strong analytic skills;
Excellent communication, planning, organizational, management skills; self-motivated, confident, creative and have a strong desire to achieve excellence;
Exceptional presentation skills, able to explain concepts concisely and accurately;
Strong interpersonal, creative thinking skills and ability to provide timely solutions to solve issues and problems;
Able to deal with different levels of internal and external stakeholders.




We offer market competitive compensation, 5-day work week, and generous benefits including medical and life insurance; and voluntary contribution in addition to the legal minimum MPF.  To apply, please send your full resume with current and expected salary to the Human Resources & Office Administration Department, Hong Kong Science and Technology Parks Corporation, 5/F, Building 5E, 5 Science Park East Avenue, Hong Kong Science Park, Hong Kong or, by email on or before 17 January 2022.   Please quote the reference number on the email subject/envelope and the application letter. 

Personal data provided will be treated in strict confidence and used for recruitment purpose only.  All personal data collected will be used strictly in accordance with employer’s personal data policies, you can access to HKSTP’s Personal Information Collection Statement at https://www.hkstp.org/hkstp_web/en/hkstp/personal-information-collection-statement-recruitment

Applicants not invited for interview within four weeks after application deadline may consider their applications unsuccessful.  Personal data of unsuccessful applicants will be retained for a maximum of two years. 

