Job Responsibilities:
Develop and maintain MIS for credit control and monitoring;
Monitor internal and external credit information system to track any negative information on existing customers, and prepare “Alert” report accordingly;  
Prepare the daily collateral monitoring reports and annual/quarterly review list;
Maintain filing system to ensure all credit review documents are properly filed and recorded;
Handle credit administration and the post loan-drawdown monitoring and control work;
Prepare and compile various credit control and monitoring reports, and ensure it is implemented in accordance with the Bank's prevailing credit strategy, policy and procedure;
Perform ad hoc assignment as and when required by Senior Management.
Job Requirements:
Degree holder in Business, Banking, Finance or related disciplines;
Minimum 5 years of relevant experiences in credit risk management,preferably have system development and credit control experience with reputable banks;
Relevant experience in Chinese Bank is a plus;
Familiar with PRC laws and regulations;
Hand-on experience in system development;
Analytical, detailed-oriented , strong numerical and business sense;
Good communication and interpersonal skills;
Able to work independently and as part of a team;
Proficient in written and spoken English and Chinese (including Putonghua).
Interested candidates please apply in full resume with earliest availability, contact number, current & expected salary to HR Department by email.


Personal data provided will be used for recruitment and related purposes, strictly in accordance with our Personal Data Policy for Applicants for Employment, a copy of which is available on request. Applicants who are not contacted within 6 weeks may consider your applications unsuccessful and the personal data collected will be destroyed after six months.

Job Responsibilities

On-site collection and follow up payback to ensure that all AR is acknowledged by customer and paid on time;
Prepare invoice, account statement and supporting documents and deliver to customer in an efficient and timely way;
Provide accurate matching of AR collection with invoice for AR clearing;
Report any bad debt or credit risk noticed;
Other ad hoc task as required.

 Job Requirements

Higher certificate or Diploma in Accounting, Finance, Business Administration, Commerce or equivalent
Good command of English and Chinese (including Putonghua)
3 years' experience in similar position
With on-site collection and retail industry experience preferred
Good communication and problem solving skills

Remuneration package will be commensurate with qualifications and experience.  Interested parties please send your application with full resume together with your expected salary to Human Resources Department by clicking "APPLY NOW".
